<section xml:id="Materials" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title> Materials</title>
  <subsection xml:id="Required-texts">
    <title>Required Texts</title>
    <p>
        Rockswold &amp; Krieger <em>&lt;Developmental Mathematics with Applications and Visualization: Prealgebra, Beginning Algebra, and Intermediate Algebra.></em> 
            2nd Edition. eText with MyLab Access. 
            ISBN-13: 9780134761985
    </p>
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="other-requirements">
    <title>Other</title>
    <p>
      You should purchase access to the <em>eText</em> with <em>MyLab</em> access from 
      Pearson. <url href="https://www.pearson.com/en-us/subject-catalog/p/developmental-mathematics-with-applications-and-visualization-prealgebra-beginning-algebra-and-intermediate-algebra/P200000006327/9780134761985">Clickable Link to Book With MyLab.</url>
    </p>
    <p>
      You will need a MyLab Access Code to access the homework assignments online as well as the eTextbook 
      for the course. After purchasing access, you will need to register for my course in MyLab, using 
      the Access Pearson tool in our LMS (Moodle). Students who do not register for MyLab by January 30th may 
      be dropped from the course.</p>

     <p> MyLab will be used to assign and collect the weekly homework assignments for this course. 
      You are allowed to work with others on homework assignments, but any work you submit should be your 
      own.

    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>